description:
Location: Hyderabad, India
Alter Domus is currently seeking a new Sales Operations Officer to join its sales Operations team at our Hyderabad Office.

JOB DESCRIPTION:

Pre-Sales activities through the Analysis of various data sets to determine Lead Generation and White Space Analysis to be shared with the Commercial team
Collate and analyze business data
Work on various Commercial reports prepared for the Commercial Leadership and beyond
Develop and establish frameworks to improve data collection and analysis to identify trends
Direct inputs in forecasting, target planning and analysis, setting and tracking of KPIs
Consolidation and reporting of data for external reporting purposes

YOUR PROFILE:

Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Business Administration or Statistics;
Expanded experience with Microsoft Excel, Power BI and possibly even Salesforce Analytics
Experience with working with large datasets and being able to structure and analyse complex and large data sets coming from different sources
Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to foster positive interaction with internal parties;
Sales oriented thought process and skills;
Ability to adapt quickly to changing priorities in a fast-paced working environment;
Familiarity with MS Office programs;
Experience with Salesforce;
Excellent attention to detail; and
Ability to work both independently and as a member of a team

- 8–12 years designing and implementing cloud data architectures on AWS (S3, Redshift, Glue, Lake Formation, IAM).

Proficient in data modeling, performance tuning, and security best practices;

AWS Certified Solutions Architect preferred.

For an international project in Chennai, we are urgently looking for a Business Analyst. Candidates need to have at least 5 years of Business Analyst and data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI) and dashboarding platforms.
We are looking for a motivated contractor. This position is long-term. Candidates need tbe fluent in English.
Tasks and responsibilities:
- Develop detailed user stories and acceptance criteria by engaging stakeholders and translating their needs into actionable development tasks;
- Facilitate effective communication between business stakeholders and technical teams to ensure project objectives and deliverables are aligned;
- Conduct comprehensive requirements gathering sessions to capture business needs, document specifications, and clarify expectations for all stakeholders;
- Design and document process flows to visualize, optimize, and align business processes with project goals;
- Collaborate with key resources to ensure user interfaces meet business requirements and enhance user experience;
- Utilize data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI) and dashboarding platforms to present findings, support decision-making, and communicate recommendations effectively;
Profile:
- Bachelor or Master degree;
- +5 years of experience working directly with clients, understanding their requirements, and delivering tailored solutions;
- Strong communication skills to effectively convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders;
- Ability to work independently and in collaboration with cross-functional teams;
- Requirements gathering and documentation;
- User story development and acceptance criteria creation;
- Stakeholder engagement and communication facilitation;
- Process flow design and business process optimization;
- User interface evaluation and enhancement;
- Proficiency in data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI) and dashboarding platforms;
- Fluent in English;
